      <div class="msgContentFrame">Excited about the next spear since I just got my Brass Spear! Time to start planning.... <br /> <br />For those looking for a Brass Spear here's the approach I took. I'm a BSM (14) and a CRP (12). I wear basic R7 gear that gives some minor bonuses to crafting. I bought a Birdsbeak Hammer and a Chocobotail Saw using leve money. I made as many components as I could as a Blacksmith and a Carpenter and bought some glue - but I still needed help with a couple parts. <br /> <br />1) - Make a Bronze Spear - the hardest part is Iron Squares and if you go to Limsa, and visit the Armor's guild, bring a couple iron nuggets, Check around to find a high enough rank armorer, ask nicely and you'll have your Iron Squares in no time at all. (If you're on Lindblum, and see me online, ping me - I now have like 20 extra Iron Squares) <br />2) While you are visiting the Armorer - also ask nicely if he'll make you some Brass Rivets (don't forget to bring a brass nugget or two with you) :) <br />3) Bring Bronze Spear, Brass Nuggets, and Brass Rivets to Goldsmith Guild in Ul'dah. Ask nicely for help making your spear. <br />4) Victory! <br /> <br />Pay your new friends well. They might not ask you for payment but it's good karma. If a recipe calls for 2xWind and 2xIce - I'll give the GSM 32xWind and 32xIce. You've just made a new friend! The spears sell for 100k+, parting with a couple grand in shards to the guys that craft all day long is something they'll appreciate. Don't push for them to mass produce (stuff from Armorer will already be made in large quantity). I know I'm always happy to help someone make something they'll wear, but I don't want to be an unpaid cog in someone else's factory. But it's certainly something you can ask if they'd like to partner with you on and share in the profits. <br /> <br />Back to planning my Iron Spear....</div>
